The paper deals with a mathematical problem related to probability distributions, specifically the Kullback-Leibler divergence between two Weibull distributions. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories within computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), signal processing (cs.SI), and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
